<div id="review_1306759190" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1306759190" />
    <a title="Nidhi Mahajan" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/19691333-nidhi-mahajan"><img alt="Nidhi Mahajan" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1640001926p2/19691333.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1306759190?book_show_action=true">Jun 13, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Nidhi Mahajan" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Nidhi Mahajan" href="/user/show/19691333-nidhi-mahajan">Nidhi Mahajan</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9788184005134" href="/book/show/23261012-our-moon-has-blood-clots">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/19691333-nidhi-mahajan?shelf=kashmir">kashmir</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/19691333-nidhi-mahajan?shelf=non-fiction">non-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/19691333-nidhi-mahajan?shelf=owned-and-read">owned-and-read</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1306759190" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12931555060223909080">This is a very difficult book to review. I&apos;ve been thinking and re-thinking about it, and I just haven&apos;t been able to collect the proper words. I put the book on the &apos;currently reading&apos; list some time ago but only read a couple of pages then. Many days later, I finally had the courage to pick it up. I read it in a day. Despite the subject-matter, it was a very gripping and fast read. <br/><br/>The book is part non-fiction, part memoir in form. It is a very powerful read for it makes you think (Those are t</span>
  <span id="freeText12931555060223909080" style="display:none">This is a very difficult book to review. I've been thinking and re-thinking about it, and I just haven't been able to collect the proper words. I put the book on the 'currently reading' list some time ago but only read a couple of pages then. Many days later, I finally had the courage to pick it up. I read it in a day. Despite the subject-matter, it was a very gripping and fast read. <br /><br />The book is part non-fiction, part memoir in form. It is a very powerful read for it makes you think (Those are the best kind of books!). I highly recommend this book if you're interested in Kashmir and the various issues surrounding it (I came to know a number of things which I didn't know/wasn't clear on before) but I would also recommend it if you are clueless about these issues (This book will make you want to know more!). <br /><br />As far as the writing is concerned, it flows. The narrative is not linear- it jumps time a lot and takes you through the memories and narratives of other people (besides the narrator). But that doesn't make the book difficult to read at all. <br /><br />A very solid read. Withheld on star only because it is the first book that I read on the subject and I am not sure if it gives a whole picture. Sometimes you can get swayed away by sentimental narratives. I want to know more.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="12931555060223909080" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


